=Compose today's edition of The Plannen Post for {{ $now.setZone("Europe/Brussels").toFormat("cccc d LLLL yyyy") }} (edition_date {{ $now.setZone("Europe/Brussels").toFormat("yyyy-LL-dd") }}).

WORKFLOW (follow exactly): In your FIRST step, issue ALL tool calls together and in parallel — the plannen tools (briefing, list_events today, list_events tomorrow, list_obligations, get_watch_queue) AND exactly 4 Web Search calls (one each: sport, news, tech, startup). Make each call ONCE. Then, in your NEXT step, compose and return the final JSON. Do NOT make any further tool calls, retries, or follow-up searches after the first step. If a feed search is empty or errors, just omit that feed.

The dateline is REQUIRED and must be filled (Weekday · DD Mon · morning edition · emoji + high°C from Digest Weather). Inbox, sent mail, digested weather+pollen, and prior memory are below. Source times are UTC (Z) — convert to Europe/Brussels.

=== INBOX (recent) ===
{{ JSON.stringify($("Aggregate Mail").first().json.emails || []) }}

=== SENT (recent — for 'no reply yet' detection) ===
{{ JSON.stringify($("Aggregate Sent").first().json.emails || []) }}

=== WEATHER + POLLEN (Mechelen, digested) ===
{{ JSON.stringify($("Digest Weather").first().json || {}) }}

=== PRIOR MEMORY (recent sidecars) ===
{{ JSON.stringify($("Read Memory").all().map(r => r.json)) }}

Return ONLY a single raw JSON object with keys dateline, edition_date, sections[], sidecar — no markdown, no code fences, no commentary.
